Quest Information
Effective Strategy: Slash Attacks, Blind/Sleep/Silence Res
Ashen King Mont has a powerful recovery that activates when he falls below half HP. In addition, he will focus on attacking units with high DEF while his HP is 40% or above.
The enemy's ability use counts and AP Consumption differ from those of a player unit Ashen King Mont.
Enemies in this quest do not drop Crystals.

Quest Information
Effective Strategy: Slash/Magic Attack, Barrier Destruction, Disable Res
It will be extremely difficult to deal damage to Crystalite Beast Muraga's body until the four appendages have been destroyed, so prioritize destroying them first.
Crystalite Beast Muraga will focus on attacking units with high DEF/SPR while his HP is 80% or above, so try to take advantage of this with a high-durability unit.
Enemies in this quest do not drop Crystals.

There are Attack Types (Slash/Pierce/Strike/Missile/Magic) and Attack Resistances. Attack a target with low resistance to your unit's Attack Type.

Attack an enemy repeatedly with the same attack type to create Type Chains which increase your damage. Type Chains are triggered when you consecutively attack an enemy with a single Attack Type (Slash/Pierce/Strike/Missile). Type Chains end if you attack the enemy with a different Attack Type or when the enemy takes its next turn. *Type Chains do not trigger for Magic type attacks.
Learn about Cast Targeting, Viewpoint Display, and Camera Rotation.
Understand the basics of TP-Consuming Abilities, AP-Consuming Abilities, and Limit Bursts.
Every unit in your party has Affinity for an element. Check each unit's Affinity before attacking.
Attacks have Elemental Types, while Units have Elemental Resistances. Attack a target with an element to which it has low Resistance.

Attack an enemy repeatedly with abilities of the same element to create Elemental Chains which increase your damage. Elemental Chains are triggered when you consecutively attack an enemy with an ability of a single elemental type (Fire/Ice/Wind/Earth/Lightning/Water/Light/Dark). Elemental Chains end if you attack the enemy with a normal attack or a different element, or when the enemy takes its next turn.
Learn how to avoid and prevent Status Ailments.
Opponents can have high Resistance to certain Status Ailments. Try inflicting a target with Status Ailments to which it has low Resistance.
Learn about height difference and the range of arching-shot fire for bows.
AGI determines how quickly a unit's turn will come. Meanwhile, ending a turn without acting will cause that unit's next turn to come more quickly. Use these tactics to your advantage in battle.
A countdown begins when the unit is KO'd. At count 0, the KO'd unit will retreat from the stage, so be careful.
Be sure to pick up Item Drops from KO'd enemies, as well as Crystals that appear after units have retreated.
Equip Espers, fill the Evocation Gauge, and activate powerful Evocation Magic.
